.TH "ELEMENT.ARIAINVALID" "3JS" "April 19, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Element.ariaInvalid \- Element: ariaInvalid property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]ariaInvalid\f[B]\f[R] property of the \f[CR]Element\f[R]
interface reflects the value of the \f[CR]aria\-invalid\f[R] attribute.
Relevant for the \f[CR]application\f[R], \f[CR]checkbox\f[R],
\f[CR]combobox\f[R], \f[CR]gridcell\f[R], \f[CR]listbox\f[R],
\f[CR]radiogroup\f[R], \f[CR]slider\f[R], \f[CR]spinbutton\f[R],
\f[CR]textbox\f[R], and \f[CR]tree\f[R] roles, it indicates to the
accessibility API whether the entered value does not conform to the
format expected by the application.
.PP
If the attribute is not present, or is set to the empty string,
assistive technology will treat the value as if it were set to
\f[CR]false\f[R].
If the attribute is present but set to a value other than
\f[CR]false\f[R], \f[CR]grammar\f[R], \f[CR]spelling\f[R] or the empty
string (\f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R]), assistive technology treats the value as
\f[CR]true\f[R].
The property reflects the attribute value as set, not as handled by
assistive technology.
.SH VALUE
A string with one of the following values:
.TP
\f[B]\(dqtrue\(dq\f[R]
The element is invalid.
.TP
\f[B]\(dqfalse\(dq\f[R] (default)
The element is not in an invalid state.
.TP
\f[B]\(dqgrammar\(dq\f[R]
The element is in an invalid state because grammatical error was
detected.
.TP
\f[B]\(dqspelling\(dq\f[R]
The element is in an invalid state because spelling error was detected.
.SH EXAMPLES
In this example the \f[CR]aria\-invalid\f[R] attribute on the element
with an ID of \f[CR]quote\f[R] is omitted, returning \f[CR]null\f[R] and
treated as \f[CR]false\f[R].
Using \f[CR]ariaInvalid\f[R] we update the value to \f[CR]grammar\f[R]
(because there are two errors).
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]div\f[R] id=\(dqquote\(dq role=\(dqtextbox\(dq contenteditable>you are your best thing..</\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] el = document.getElementById(\(dqquote\(dq);
log(\(gaInitial value: ${el.ariaInvalid}\(ga);
el.ariaInvalid = \(dqgrammar\(dq;
log(\(gaUpdated value: ${el.ariaInvalid}\(ga);
.EE
